Yes.  It is frustrating when I'm getting ready to watch a movie, and I get
up 5 or 6 times during the movie and have to take care of something.  I
remember not too long ago when it took me like 4 hours to watch a 1 hour
show I recorded...kept hitting pause to go do something (that in reality
could have waited).  I'm also bad about having to use sticky notes so I
don't forget (like the world will end if I forget something as simple as a
movie preview I want to see...I have to write it down right that
minute)...drives me nuts.  I think that is signs of OCD.  I also have
trouble if someone hurts my feelings...can't let it go.  Normal friends just
shrug it off or by the next day are not so much thinking of an argument, but
I have held on to an issue that happened a year ago and I think about it
almost every day..geeze!
Cougar

