That's just it...the replaying over and over like you are in a movie that is
stuck.  Sometimes I can focus on something else to get my mind off of the
situation and sometimes when I am trying to relax, that tape in my head
plays over and over.  The thing is that sometimes the images in my mind are
not nice.  They are scary images I have seen on tv or bizarre things.  Maybe
like something from my past like seeing my Dad dead or weird out of the blue
stuff like that.  I hate it, and that's why I am seeing help again, even
though I had been stable off meds for like 5 years...this isn't right, and
it is interfering with the quality of my life.  I'm not sure if it is
bipolar, Schizoaffective, OCD or just pure anxiety.  All I know is that I am
not sleeping or resting and feeling &quot;tired but wired&quot; for like weeks/months
at a time.
